        "category": "ancestry",
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per day</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> You would fail a save against a spell or effect with the void trait.</p><hr /><p>The darkness between the stars isn't simply a void for your people, it's a storehouse for a great reserve of energy, built by generation after generation of maraquois. When the darkness threatens to take hold of you, the power of that ancestral wellspring swells forth and lifts you up. You reroll the triggering saving throw with a +1 status bonus. You must use the second result, even if it's worse.</p>"
